        {
          "insert": "The Cut"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-30-docs-server-embeddable-decision-16": {
      "id": "b-30-docs-server-embeddable-decision-16",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "kind": "Package boundary",
        "title": "Embeddable in host apps",
        "tone": "decision"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Host embeddability is the forcing constraint. A host mounts the "
        },
        {
          "insert": "/api/*",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " route factory in its own Elysia server and brings its own UI. A dependency on "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs-viewer — rendering and editing",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/10-packages/40-docs-viewer"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " or React would force every host to carry the browser stack."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-30-docs-server-headless-17": {
      "id": "b-30-docs-server-headless-17",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The server owns filesystem and concurrency policy, not application identity. Project lookup, authentication, process lifetime, routing outside "
        },
        {
          "insert": "/api/*",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", and UI composition remain host responsibilities."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-30-docs-server-boundary-review-18": {
      "id": "b-30-docs-server-boundary-review-18",
      "type": "callout",
      "props": {
        "kind": "Open call",
        "title": "docs-index may fold into docs-server",
        "tone": "info"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Folding "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs-index — Backlinks",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/10-packages/20-docs-index"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " into docs-server is a live candidate because both are Bun-only and the server is the index's main consumer. The current split is a judgment call: the index is derived, rebuildable state with no HTTP surface and remains useful to the CLI without a server."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
